NUMBER ONE RETAILERS,

00:14:00,139 --> 00:14:02,475
AND I THINK THIS IS GREAT
FOR THE PRODUCT.

00:14:02,475 --> 00:14:05,445
THANK YOU.
WE WISH YOU THE BEST OF LUCK
AND ALL OF US MUCH SUCCESS.

00:14:05,445 --> 00:14:07,447
(Lisa) A YEAR AGO,
MY FAMILY AND I

00:14:07,447 --> 00:14:09,449
WERE IN DANGER
OF LOSING OUR HOME.

00:14:09,449 --> 00:14:11,984
AND SINCE DOING THE DEAL
WITH DAYMOND AND BARBARA,

00:14:11,984 --> 00:14:14,721
THAT IS NO LONGER A THREAT.

00:14:14,721 --> 00:14:16,322
♪♪

00:14:25,198 --> 00:14:28,301
<i>NEXT INTO THE SHARK TANK</i>
<i>IS TIM GAVERN</i>

00:14:28,301 --> 00:14:30,303
<i>WITH A BUSINESS HE BELIEVES</i>

00:14:30,303 --> 00:14:33,306
<i>WILL BRING OUT THE KID</i>
<i>IN EVERYONE.</i>

00:14:33,306 --> 00:14:36,743
♪♪

00:14:36,943 --> 00:14:39,445
HI, I'M TIM GAVERN.

00:14:39,445 --> 00:14:42,682
MY MISSION IS TO BRING HAPPINESS
TO KIDS EVERYWHERE.

00:14:42,682 --> 00:14:45,251
(clicks button, starts engine)

00:14:45,251 --> 00:14:47,687
I'M CAPTAIN ICE CREAM.

00:14:47,687 --> 00:14:51,124
♪♪

00:14:51,124 --> 00:14:53,126
ICE CREAM TRUCKS ARE EVERYWHERE,

00:14:53,126 --> 00:14:55,128
BUT WHAT MAKES
CAPTAIN ICE CREAM SPECIAL

00:14:55,128 --> 00:14:58,197
IS MY ICE CREAM MOPED.

00:14:58,197 --> 00:15:01,334
NO ONE ELSE
HAS ANYTHING LIKE IT.

00:15:01,334 --> 00:15:04,070
ICE CREAM IS MY BLOOD.

00:15:04,070 --> 00:15:06,072
I'M A THIRD‐GENERATION
ICE CREAM VENDOR.

00:15:06,072 --> 00:15:09,108
MY MOTHER AND MY GRANDMOTHER
BOTH HAD ICE CREAM PARLORS.

00:15:09,108 --> 00:15:12,945
IT'S BEEN A TRADITION
IN OUR FAMILY SINCE THE 1950s.
HOW YOU DOING?

00:15:12,945 --> 00:15:15,448
I WAS A CAR MAGAZINE EDITOR
FOR MANY YEARS,

00:15:15,448 --> 00:15:17,450
AND THE PUBLISHING INDUSTRY
WAS ON A DOWNTURN.

00:15:17,450 --> 00:15:20,019
SO I WAS LOOKING
FOR A WAY TO MAKE MONEY.

00:15:20,019 --> 00:15:22,021
AND ICE CREAM WAS A NATURAL.

00:15:22,021 --> 00:15:24,524
I WANTED TO BRING BACK
THAT WHOLESOME, CLEAN‐CUT,

00:15:24,524 --> 00:15:27,994
NOSTALGIC IMAGE
OF THE ICE CREAM MAN

00:15:27,994 --> 00:15:30,630
THAT I REMEMBER AS A KID.
<i>(bell dings)</i>

00:15:30,630 --> 00:15:32,899
KIDS ABSOLUTELY LOVE
CAPTAIN ICE CREAM.

00:15:32,899 --> 00:15:34,434
(cheering)

00:15:34,434 --> 00:15:37,537
WHEN THEY HEAR THE BELLS,
SEE ME COMING,

00:15:37,537 --> 00:15:40,039
THEY JUMP UP AND DOWN.
THANK YOU!

00:15:40,039 --> 00:15:42,608
ME! ME! ME! ME!
THE LOOKS ON THEIR FACES‐‐

00:15:42,608 --> 00:15:45,011
THAT'S WHAT MAKES ME WANT
TO DO THIS FOREVER.

00:15:45,011 --> 00:15:46,546
ICE CREAM MAKES PEOPLE HAPPY.

00:15:46,546 --> 00:15:49,649
BUT WITH A LITTLE HELP
FROM THE SHARKS,

00:15:49,649 --> 00:15:51,184
I CAN FRANCHISE THIS BUSINESS.

00:15:51,184 --> 00:15:54,187
AND MY ULTIMATE GOAL IS TO HAVE
A CAPTAIN ICE CREAM FRANCHISE

00:15:54,187 --> 00:15:57,089
IN EVERY LITTLE TOWN
ACROSS THE UNITED STATES.

00:15:57,089 --> 00:16:00,026
(children)
THANK YOU, CAPTAIN ICE CREAM!

00:16:00,026 --> 00:16:03,095
♪♪

00:16:05,031 --> 00:16:06,833
(bell dings)

00:16:14,974 --> 00:16:16,309
(laughs)

00:16:16,309 --> 00:16:21,180
♪♪

00:16:21,180 --> 00:16:23,015
HELLO.

00:16:23,015 --> 00:16:26,819
MY NAME IS TIM GAVERN.
I'M CAPTAIN ICE CREAM.

00:16:26,819 --> 00:16:28,521
<i>(bell dings)</i>

00:16:28,521 --> 00:16:30,523
IN EXCHANGE FOR $48,000,

00:16:30,523 --> 00:16:32,525
I'M OFFERING A 25% PARTNERSHIP

00:16:32,525 --> 00:16:35,428
IN THE CAPTAIN ICE CREAM
EXPERIENCE.

00:16:35,428 --> 00:16:37,430
CAPTAIN ICE CREAM IS A MOBILE

00:16:37,430 --> 00:16:38,965
NOVELTY ICE CREAM VENDING
BUSINESS.

00:16:38,965 --> 00:16:41,734
CAPTAIN ICE CREAM WILL BE
A FRANCHISE

00:16:41,734 --> 00:16:44,070
OF MY UNIQUE ICE CREAM MOPEDS

00:16:44,070 --> 00:16:45,571
AND WILL ALSO BECOME

00:16:45,571 --> 00:16:49,542
THE NEXT BIG
NOVELTY ICE CREAM BRAND.

00:16:49,542 --> 00:16:51,377
CAPTAIN ICE CREAM FRANCHISEES

00:16:51,377 --> 00:16:53,513
WILL PROJECT A POSITIVE,
WHOLESOME IMAGE

00:16:53,513 --> 00:16:55,515
BY RIDING
MY UNIQUE ICE CREAM MOPEDS

00:16:55,515 --> 00:16:58,818
WEARING TRADITIONAL WHITE
CAPTAIN ICE CREAM UNIFORMS

00:16:58,818 --> 00:17:01,687
AND PAPER ICE CREAM HATS.

00:17:01,687 --> 00:17:04,824
DO YOU OWN A NATIONAL TRADEMARK
FOR THE CAPTAIN ICE CREAM‐‐

00:17:04,824 --> 00:17:07,293
YES, I OWN THE TRADEMARK.
IF YOU HAVE
THE NATIONAL TRADEMARK,

00:17:07,293 --> 00:17:10,930
THAT MEANS NOBODY ELSE CAN CALL
THEMSELVES CAPTAIN ICE CREAM.

00:17:10,930 --> 00:17:13,332
DO YOU HAVE ANY ICE CREAM
TO GIVE US?
OF COURSE.

00:17:13,332 --> 00:17:16,235
(Robert) CAN I HAVE SOME?
SURE. WOULD YOU ALL LIKE SOME?

00:17:16,235 --> 00:17:20,273
(Daymond) YOU SHOULDA DONE THAT
A LONG TIME AGO.
I'M GONNA GIVE YOU
MY NUMBER ONE SELLING PRODUCT.

00:17:20,273 --> 00:17:22,909
CAPTAIN, BREAK OPEN THE BOX.
THERE WE GO. NOW WE'RE TALKING.
<i>(bell dings)</i>

00:17:22,909 --> 00:17:25,711
TIM, I WANT TO BE CLEAR.
DID YOU MAKE THIS ICE CREAM?

00:17:25,711 --> 00:17:28,114
NO. THIS IS BOUGHT
FROM A COMPANY.

00:17:28,114 --> 00:17:31,450
BUT THIS IS ABSOLUTELY
MY NUMBER ONE PRODUCT.
IT'S DELICIOUS.

00:17:31,450 --> 00:17:33,486
CAPTAIN, WHAT DOES IT COST
TO MAKE THE, UM,

00:17:33,486 --> 00:17:37,256
CAPTAIN ICE CREAM MOPED?
A BRAND‐NEW VERSION OF THIS
WILL COST ABOUT $7,000.

00:17:37,256 --> 00:17:39,258
SO WHAT'S THE BUSINESS MODEL?

00:17:39,258 --> 00:17:41,561
HOW MUCH DO YOU SELL
IN A DAY, CAPTAIN?

00:17:41,561 --> 00:17:46,432
UM, GENERALLY ABOUT $200 WORTH
OF ICE CREAM IN‐‐IN 4 HOURS.

00:17:46,432 --> 00:17:48,901
OH...

00:17:48,901 --> 00:17:51,537
I JUST WANT TO BE CLEAR.

00:17:51,537 --> 00:17:53,072
$200 A DAY?

00:17:53,072 --> 00:17:55,074
(Barbara) FOUR HOURS.
IN‐‐IN FOUR HOURS.

00:17:55,074 --> 00:17:57,610
GENERALLY AN EVENT IS‐‐
IS FOUR HOURS.
WHAT'S YOUR PROFIT?

00:17:57,610 --> 00:18:01,147
IT'S EASY TO MAKE
$25 PER HOUR AS A VENDOR.

00:18:01,147 --> 00:18:04,483
BUT WHAT'S THE BUSINESS MODEL
FOR ME AS AN INVESTOR?

00:18:04,483 --> 00:18:08,187
YOU WANT $48,000 FOR WHAT?
I WANT TO BUILD
A COUPLE OF MOPEDS.

00:18:08,187 --> 00:18:11,691
I WANT TO START WORKING ON
AN ELECTRIC VERSION OF THIS.

00:18:11,691 --> 00:18:14,126
OKAY?
HOW MANY DO YOU HAVE NOW?
HOW MANY MOPEDS?

00:18:14,126 --> 00:18:16,262
THIS IS IT.
JUST THE ONE?

00:18:16,262 --> 00:18:18,764
AND ARE YOU MAKING A LIVING?

00:18:18,764 --> 00:18:23,002
I'M‐‐I'M BARELY
EKING OUT A LIVING.
DO YOU THINK THAT'S A PROBLEM

00:18:23,002 --> 00:18:25,471
WHEN YOU'RE TRYING TO SELL IT
TO OTHER FRANCHISEES,

00:18:25,471 --> 00:18:29,075
AND YOU'RE BARELY MAKING
A LIVING?
I DON'T, BECAUSE I'M STILL
LEARNING THE BUSINESS.

00:18:29,075 --> 00:18:32,678
OKAY, YOU SAID YOU'RE GONNA
FRANCHISE THIS.

00:18:32,678 --> 00:18:35,314
HAVE YOU HIRED
ANY FRANCHISE LAWYERS?
(laughs)

00:18:35,314 --> 00:18:38,784
DO YOU HAVE DOCUMENTS PREPARED?
ANYTHING LIKE THAT?
KEVIN, HE'S MAKING $25
AN HOUR SELLING ICE CREAM.

00:18:38,784 --> 00:18:40,753
(Harrington) RIGHT.
RIGHT NOW I'M SELLING...

00:18:40,753 --> 00:18:43,389
A CONCEPT.
SEVERAL DIFFERENT BRANDS‐‐

00:18:43,389 --> 00:18:45,491
YOU'RE REALLY SELLING A CONCEPT
RIGHT NOW, AREN'T YOU?
EXACTLY. EXACTLY.

00:18:45,491 --> 00:18:47,793
YES. IF I BUY
A FRANCHISE FROM YOU,

00:18:47,793 --> 00:18:49,629
LET ME WALK IN THAT GUY'S SHOES.
OKAY.

00:18:49,629 --> 00:18:52,465
HOW MUCH COULD I REASONABLY
EXPECT TO EARN IF I WAS WORKING

00:18:52,465 --> 00:18:54,934
FOUR HOURS A DAY,
FIVE DAYS A WEEK?

00:18:54,934 --> 00:18:58,204
BECAUSE THAT'S THE NUMBER
YOU THREW OUT, FOUR HOURS‐‐
MORE THAN YOU'RE MAKING
IN REAL ESTATE TODAY.

00:18:58,204 --> 00:18:59,805
(Barbara) PROBABLY. (laughs)
(laughs)

00:18:59,805 --> 00:19:01,974
YOU COULD EASILY MAKE $25,000
TO $50,000 A YEAR

00:19:01,974 --> 00:19:03,643
AS AN ICE CREAM PERSON.

00:19:03,643 --> 00:19:06,379
I GET WHAT YOU'RE DOING.
YOU SELL ICE CREAM.

00:19:06,379 --> 00:19:09,548
BUT I DON'T KNOW WHERE
THE INVESTMENT OPPORTUNITY IS,

00:19:09,548 --> 00:19:12,752
BECAUSE ANYBODY CAN MAKE
A MOPED WITH A FREEZER ON IT.
YEAH, BUT CAN THEY?

00:19:12,752 --> 00:19:15,554
THAT'S THE THING.
CAN THEY? YOU KNOW‐‐
YEAH, THEY CAN.

00:19:18,290 --> 00:19:21,060
(Daymond)
TIM, I THINK IT'S A‐A CRIME

00:19:21,060 --> 00:19:23,562
FOR ME TO INSULT
AN ICE CREAM MAN.

00:19:23,562 --> 00:19:25,064
I THINK THERE'S SOMETHING

00:19:25,064 --> 00:19:27,433
JUST INNOCENT AND BEAUTIFUL
ABOUT AN ICE CREAM MAN.

00:19:27,433 --> 00:19:29,402
I CAN APPRECIATE THAT.
THANK YOU.

00:19:29,402 --> 00:19:31,404
BUT THE BUSINESS
IS NOT BIG ENOUGH FOR ME.

00:19:31,404 --> 00:19:33,839
BUT I DO LOVE YOUR, UH,
YOUR‐‐YOUR ATTITUDE

00:19:33,839 --> 00:19:35,841
AND WHAT YOU WANT TO DO,

00:19:35,841 --> 00:19:40,046
BUT I'M OUT.
I DON'T UNDERSTAND THAT, BEC‐‐
ALL RIGHT, THINK ABOUT IT.

00:19:40,046 --> 00:19:43,049
OKAY, IT'S A VERY INEXPENSIVE
FRANCHISE‐‐
WELL, THINK ABOUT
MY POINT OF VIEW.

00:19:43,049 --> 00:19:47,119
ALL I CARE ABOUT IS,
HOW DO I GET MY MONEY BACK?
WELL, YOU GET YOUR MONEY BACK
IN TWO DIFFERENT WAYS.

00:19:47,119 --> 00:19:50,156
HOW?
FIRST OF ALL,
SAY THE FRANCHISE IS $12,500

00:19:50,156 --> 00:19:52,324
TO BE A FRANCHISEE
OF CAPTAIN ICE CREAM.

00:19:52,324 --> 00:19:54,460
OKAY, SO‐‐
WHY WOULD ANYBODY GIVE YOU
$12,000 WHEN THEY COULD JUST‐‐

00:19:54,460 --> 00:19:57,463
WHY NOT? YOU'RE GONNA SELL THEM
ICE CREAM AT A DISCOUNT

00:19:57,463 --> 00:20:00,933
THAT'S GONNA BE
THEIR OWN BRANDED ICE CREAM.
BUT THEY COULD
BUY ICE CREAM <i>ANYWHERE.</i>

00:20:00,933 --> 00:20:04,637
LOOK, YOU'VE GOT A CONCEPT
OF WHICH NOTHING IS...

00:20:04,637 --> 00:20:06,772
UNIQUE AND PATENTABLE OR‐‐

00:20:06,772 --> 00:20:09,909
YOU DON'T THINK
THIS IS UNIQUE?
ADMIT IT. IT'S UNIQUE.

00:20:09,909 --> 00:20:13,112
AT LEAST GIVE THE GUY THAT.
IT'S ABSOLUTELY UNIQUE.

00:20:13,112 --> 00:20:15,114
ALL RIGHT, YOU KNOW
WHAT I'VE DECIDED?

00:20:15,114 --> 00:20:17,383
I'M GONNA GIVE‐‐
I'M GONNA GIVE YOU $48,000

00:20:17,383 --> 00:20:19,719
OF BARBARA'S MONEY.
(laughs)

00:20:19,719 --> 00:20:22,788
(laughs)
YOU KNOW,
I‐‐I'M HOLDING MYSELF BACK,

00:20:22,788 --> 00:20:25,691
BECAUSE I BELIEVE IN CHILDREN
AND WONDERFUL, WARM AND‐‐

00:20:25,691 --> 00:20:27,693
AND THINGS FROM THE PAST.

00:20:27,693 --> 00:20:29,795
THAT'S WHAT I'M TRYING
TO RECREATE HERE.
BUT‐‐BUT I CAN'T MAKE
ANY MONEY.

00:20:29,795 --> 00:20:31,964
AND I WANT YOU
TO GET BACK ON THAT THING

00:20:31,964 --> 00:20:34,967
AND RIDE INTO THE SUNSET,
BECAUSE‐‐
I DON'T THINK
THAT'S TRUE, THOUGH,

00:20:34,967 --> 00:20:37,636
BECAUSE YOU'RE GONNA TAKE
A FRANCHISE FEE...
NO, I REALLY DO BECAUSE,
I HAVE TO‐‐HERE'S THE PROBLEM‐‐

00:20:37,636 --> 00:20:40,940
AND YOU'RE GONNA MAKE A PROFIT
ON EVERY BIKE.
HERE'S THE BUSINESS REALITY
IN THIS.

00:20:40,940 --> 00:20:44,310
OKAY.
IN ABOUT FIVE MINUTES, I'M GONNA
HAVE TO SEND YOU AN INVOICE

00:20:44,310 --> 00:20:46,312
FOR ABOUT $2,000 FOR MY TIME.
(laughs)

00:20:46,312 --> 00:20:50,049
I GONNA TAKE OFF 50 CENTS
FOR THE ICE CREAM, THOUGH.
OKAY. IT'S $1.50, BY THE WAY.

00:20:50,049 --> 00:20:53,219
$1.50? THAT'S AN OUTRAGE.
ARE YOU KIDDING?
IT'S A 400% MARKUP
ON ICE CREAM.

00:20:53,219 --> 00:20:56,589
THERE'S JUST NOTHING HERE.
THAT'S THE PROBLEM.
(Daymond) SAY THE WORD.

00:20:56,589 --> 00:20:58,090
I'M OUT.

00:20:58,090 --> 00:21:00,993
I WANT TO SUMMARIZE
WHAT YOU'VE TOLD ME,

00:21:00,993 --> 00:21:02,995
JUST SO I'M CLEAR.
OKAY, SURE.

00:21:02,995 --> 00:21:05,231
YOU BARELY MAKE ANY MONEY
DOING THIS TODAY.

00:21:05,231 --> 00:21:09,068
YOU DON'T MAKE THE ICE CREAM.
NOT YET.
I'M WORKING ON IT.

00:21:09,068 --> 00:21:11,871
YOU HAVEN'T SOLD
A SINGLE FRANCHISE.

00:21:11,871 --> 00:21:14,240
AND YOU HAVE
A LONG WAY TO GO.

00:21:14,240 --> 00:21:17,476
IT'S A START‐UP.
WHAT AM I GONNA TELL YOU?

00:21:17,476 --> 00:21:20,246
UM, THE ICE CREAM GAVE ME
A BRAIN FREEZE. I'M OUT.

00:21:22,615 --> 00:21:25,751
TIM, I UNDERSTAND WHAT
YOU'RE TRYING TO DO,

00:21:25,751 --> 00:21:27,920
BUT YOU HAVE
NO FRANCHISE COMPANY, OKAY?

00:21:27,920 --> 00:21:31,490
IT'S A SMALL BUSINESS.
THANK YOU FOR‐‐FOR COMING HERE
TODAY, BUT I'M OUT.

00:21:33,592 --> 00:21:36,228
I THINK I'D HAPPILY BUY
ICE CREAM FROM YOU.

00:21:36,228 --> 00:21:38,898
YOU SEEM LIKE THE PERFECT
ICE CREAM KIND OF GUY.

00:21:38,898 --> 00:21:41,834
BUT YOU'RE HERE TOO EARLY,
YOU'RE HERE TOO UNPREPARED.

00:21:41,834 --> 00:21:44,003
I'M OUT.

00:21:44,003 --> 00:21:45,704
THANK YOU, TIM.

00:21:45,704 --> 00:21:48,707
ALL RIGHT. THANK YOU, ALL.
I APPRECIATE YOUR TIME.
(Robert) ALL RIGHT.

00:21:48,707 --> 00:21:50,209
ALL RIGHT. THANK YOU.

00:21:59,351 --> 00:22:01,854
I DON'T THINK THE SHARKS
SAW THE BEAUTY IN...

00:22:01,854 --> 00:22:03,956
WHAT THIS BUSINESS COULD BE.

00:22:03,956 --> 00:22:06,125
I‐‐I'M A LITTLE DISAPPOINTED.

00:22:08,260 --> 00:22:09,395
(laughs)

00:22:09,395 --> 00:22:12,264
HE'S GOT A LOT
OF ICE CREAM IN HERE.

00:22:12,264 --> 00:22:15,534
OKAY, GET OUT OF THE WAY.
I'M GONNA START IT.
KICK IT.
KICK IT UP, BABY.

00:22:15,534 --> 00:22:18,537
BOYS WILL BOYS.
(laughing)

00:22:18,537 --> 00:22:21,240
I'M LEAVING. (laughs)

00:22:21,240 --> 00:22:23,943
(laughs)
(O'Leary) BYE‐BYE.

00:22:23,943 --> 00:22:24,944
LATER!

00:22:24,944 --> 00:22:28,347
(imitates engine revving)

00:22:40,125 --> 00:22:42,127
♪♪

00:22:42,127 --> 00:22:44,129
<i>NEXT UP IS MICHAEL SCHIAVONE,</i>

00:22:44,129 --> 00:22:47,032
<i>WITH AN INNOVATIVE</i>
<i>BUSINESS STRATEGY</i>

00:22:47,032 --> 00:22:49,735
<i>HE HOPES WILL SEND THE SHARKS</i>
<i>INTO A FRENZY.</i>

00:22:49,735 --> 00:22:52,738
♪♪

00:23:00,512 --> 00:23:02,548
HELLO.
MY NAME IS MICHAEL SCHIAVONE.

00:23:02,548 --> 00:23:05,918
I CALL MY IDEA CAFFEINDICATOR.

00:23:05,918 --> 00:23:07,920
AND I'M SEEKING $200,000

00:23:07,920 --> 00:23:12,491
IN EXCHANGE FOR A 25%
EQUITY POSITION IN THIS VENTURE.

00:23:12,491 --> 00:23:15,361
NOW DID YOU EVER WONDER WHY
THERE'S A DECAF MARKET?

00:23:15,361 --> 00:23:18,030
IT'S EITHER BECAUSE PEOPLE
DON'T WANT CAFFEINE

00:23:18,030 --> 00:23:21,634
OR CAN'T HAVE CAFFEINE FOR
MEDICAL OR FOR PERSONAL REASONS.

00:23:21,634 --> 00:23:23,102
THE FACT IS,

00:23:23,102 --> 00:23:26,438
YOU DON'T KNOW WHETHER THERE'S
CAFFEINE IN YOUR COFFEE OR NOT.

00:23:26,438 --> 00:23:28,440
ENTER CAFFEINDICATOR.

00:23:28,440 --> 00:23:30,643
IT'S THE FIRST
LITMUS‐LIKE TESTER

00:23:30,643 --> 00:23:32,645
INCORPORATED
ON A SWEETENER PACKET

00:23:32,645 --> 00:23:35,147
WHICH CHANGES COLOR
IN THE PRESENCE OF CAFFEINE.

00:23:35,147 --> 00:23:38,250
IS IT INK IN THE PAPER
OR IN THE SUGAR?
IT'S ON THE PAPER.
IT'S AN INK.

00:23:38,250 --> 00:23:41,520
IT'S MICROENCAPSULATED
IN GELATIN.
(Robert) BUT, MICHAEL,
DOES IT REALLY WORK?

00:23:41,520 --> 00:23:43,756
OH, CERTAINLY IT DOES WORK.
ABSOLUTELY.

00:23:43,756 --> 00:23:47,459
LET ME DEMONSTRATE
A MOCK PROTOTYPE.

00:23:47,459 --> 00:23:51,196
AS YOU CAN SEE, IF THERE'S
CAFFEINE IN THE COFFEE,

00:23:51,196 --> 00:23:53,966
IT WILL TURN PINK.

00:23:53,966 --> 00:23:57,102
IT'S DYNAMIC. IT'S CURIOUS.

00:23:57,102 --> 00:23:58,671
IT'S FUN TO SHARE.

00:23:58,671 --> 00:24:01,674
AND HEY, I DON'T EVEN USE
A SWEETENER IN MY COFFEE,

00:24:01,674 --> 00:24:03,776
BUT I JUST USED A PACKET.

00:24:03,776 --> 00:24:07,813
THE SWEETENER PACKET MARKET IS
ROUGHLY A $12‐BILLION MARKET,

00:24:07,813 --> 00:24:10,015
OF WHICH, THE BLUE GUYS
HAVE MARKET SHARE,

00:24:10,015 --> 00:24:12,117
THE PINK GUYS
HAVE MARKET SHARE,

00:24:12,117 --> 00:24:13,953
THE GREEN GUYS
HAVE MARKET SHARE,

00:24:13,953 --> 00:24:15,821
THE YELLOW GUYS
HAVE MARKET SHARE,

00:24:15,821 --> 00:24:18,457
AND THE WHITE GUYS
HAVE MARKET SHARE.

00:24:18,457 --> 00:24:21,460
NOW WHAT WOULD HAPPEN IF
ANY ONE OF THESE MANUFACTURERS

00:24:21,460 --> 00:24:23,462
WERE ABLE TO DRAMATICALLY
INCREASE THEIR SHARE

00:24:23,462 --> 00:24:25,831
IN THIS GLOBAL MARKET?

00:24:25,831 --> 00:24:28,200
DOES THAT HAVE VALUE?
YES.

00:24:28,200 --> 00:24:29,668
OF COURSE IT DOES.

00:24:29,668 --> 00:24:31,670
SHARKS, WELCOME TO
THE SUGAR BOWL BRAWL.

00:24:31,670 --> 00:24:35,107
THESE GUYS ARE ALL FIGHTING
FOR MARKET SHARE.

00:24:35,107 --> 00:24:38,110
SO WHAT DOES IT TAKE
TO TAKE A $500‐MILLION PRODUCT

00:24:38,110 --> 00:24:42,448
TO A $1‐BILLION PRODUCT?

00:24:42,448 --> 00:24:45,484
BUT IS THERE AN INDICATION
OF IT HEAVILY CAFFEINATED

00:24:45,484 --> 00:24:47,553
OR WHATEVER THE CASE IS?

00:24:47,553 --> 00:24:49,555
NO, IT DOESN'T TELL ME
HOW MUCH CAFFEINE.

00:24:49,555 --> 00:24:52,224
IT TELLS ME WHETHER OR NOT
THERE IS CAFFEINE.
ALMOST LIKE A PREGNANCY TEST‐‐

00:24:52,224 --> 00:24:55,227
VERY SIMILAR. IN FACT,
THAT WAS PART OF THE‐‐

00:24:55,227 --> 00:24:58,230
BUT DOESN'T‐‐DOESN'T DECAF‐‐
HAS ABOUT 2 MILLIGRAMS
OF CAFFEINE IN IT.

00:24:58,230 --> 00:25:01,633
YOU'RE ABSOLUTELY RIGHT,
VERSUS 120 MILLIGRAMS.
BUT IT'S STILL
GONNA TRIGGER THE TEST.

00:25:01,633 --> 00:25:05,104
I CAN MASK OUT
THE FALSE POSITIVES.
(Robert) YOU'RE MISSING
THE POINT OF THIS.

00:25:05,104 --> 00:25:08,107
IT DOESN'T MATTER WHETHER
THE PERSON WANTS TO KNOW

00:25:08,107 --> 00:25:10,009
WHETHER THERE'S CAFFEINE OR NOT.

00:25:10,009 --> 00:25:12,311
IT'S THE FACT THAT THE WHITE GUY
CAN SAY TO THE YELLOW GUY,

00:25:12,311 --> 00:25:14,980
"MY PACKET'S BETTER
BECAUSE IT DOES THIS."
I GET IT. I GET THAT.

00:25:14,980 --> 00:25:16,782
(O'Leary) AND I AGREE WITH YOU.
THAT'S IT!

00:25:16,782 --> 00:25:19,752
(Michael) THAT'S WHY I'M HERE.
THIS IS A GREAT OPPORTUNITY.

00:25:19,752 --> 00:25:21,754
THE MANUFACTURING
AND THE DISTRIBUTION

00:25:21,754 --> 00:25:24,757
IS ALREADY IN PLACE.

00:25:24,757 --> 00:25:27,760
WHAT WE'RE LEVERAGING IS MARKET
SHARE IN A GLOBAL INDUSTRY.

00:25:27,760 --> 00:25:29,895
AND I'D LIKE TO KNOW
IF YOU'RE INTERESTED

00:25:29,895 --> 00:25:32,197
IN PARTNERING WITH ME
ON THIS VENTURE.

00:25:32,197 --> 00:25:34,633
SO, MICHAEL, WHEN YOU WENT
TO THE BLUE GUYS,

00:25:34,633 --> 00:25:36,802
AND SAID,
"I HAVE THIS GREAT IDEA,

00:25:36,802 --> 00:25:40,672
BUY MY PRODUCT,"
WHAT DID THEY SAY?

00:25:40,672 --> 00:25:42,775
I HAVE NOT GONE
TO THE BLUE GUYS YET.
WHY NOT?

00:25:42,775 --> 00:25:45,377
I CAME TO YOU GUYS TO SEE
IF YOU CAN OPEN THE DOORS

00:25:45,377 --> 00:25:47,379
AND PARTNER WITH ME IN‐‐
ON THIS.

00:25:47,379 --> 00:25:50,049
YOU'VE NEVER TRIED TO TALK TO
ANY OF THE WHITE, YELLOW,

00:25:50,049 --> 00:25:52,151
GREEN, PINK, BLUE GUYS?
NO, SIR. I HAVE NOT.

00:25:52,151 --> 00:25:54,653
AND DO YOU OWN THE PATENT‐‐
I DO.

00:25:54,653 --> 00:25:58,690
HOW MUCH WILL THIS ADD
TO THE COST OF EACH PACKET?

00:25:58,690 --> 00:26:01,093
IT HAS TO BE NEGLIGIBLE.
(Robert) YOU DON'T KNOW
THE NUMBER?

00:26:01,093 --> 00:26:03,462
UH, UH, NO. THE FACT
OF THE MATTER

00:26:03,462 --> 00:26:05,464
IS THAT ANYTHING YOU MAKE
IN MASS QUANTITY,

00:26:05,464 --> 00:26:08,434
THE‐‐THE‐‐THE‐‐THE PRICE
OF IT DROPS.

00:26:08,434 --> 00:26:11,570
WHAT'S YOUR COST
TO MAKE ONE PACK NOW?
I DON'T HAVE A COST TO MAKE
ONE PACK RIGHT NOW.

00:26:11,570 --> 00:26:14,973
WHAT‐‐GIVE US A NUMBER. WE JUST
WANT A FEEL FOR THE NUMBER.
(Robert) VOLUME‐‐YEAH.

00:26:14,973 --> 00:26:17,042
HERE'S MY THOUGHT ON THAT.

00:26:17,042 --> 00:26:19,044
UM, IF I INCREASE
MARKET SHARE DRAMATICALLY,

00:26:19,044 --> 00:26:21,880
THE COST OF PRODUCTION
GOES DOWN, PROFIT GOES UP.
(Barbara) YES.

00:26:21,880 --> 00:26:24,850
GIVE US A NUMBER.
YEAH, WE‐‐WE GET THAT,
BUT CAN IT BE MADE

00:26:24,850 --> 00:26:28,153
FOR A FRACTION OF PENNIES MORE?

00:26:28,153 --> 00:26:30,022
ABSOLUTELY.
IT CAN?

00:26:30,022 --> 00:26:32,558
ABSOLUTELY.
SO, MICHAEL,
WHAT YOU'VE DONE, BASICALLY,

00:26:32,558 --> 00:26:35,294
IS YOU DEFINED
YOUR ENTIRE MARKET.

00:26:35,294 --> 00:26:39,431
THAT'S GOOD. IT'S VERY CLEAR
WHO WE HAVE TO SELL IT TO.

00:26:39,431 --> 00:26:42,868
THE BAD IS, IT'S VERY CLEAR
WHO WE HAVE TO SELL IT TO.

00:26:42,868 --> 00:26:47,406
IF ONE OF THESE COLOR
DON'T BUY YOUR PRODUCT,

00:26:47,406 --> 00:26:49,842
THERE IS NO MARKET.
WOULD YOU AGREE?

00:26:49,842 --> 00:26:51,844
THAT'S CORRECT.

00:26:51,844 --> 00:26:55,447
BUT WAIT A MINUTE. YOUR STRATEGY
IS TO GO TO ALL FIVE AND SAY,

00:26:55,447 --> 00:26:58,450
"WHICH ONE OF YOU WANTS TO
INCREASE YOUR MARKET SHARE?"

00:26:58,450 --> 00:27:01,286
SO THE REAL QUESTION
ON YOUR DEAL IS,

00:27:01,286 --> 00:27:03,755
IF I'M ONE OF THESE
MARKETEER MANUFACTURERS,

00:27:03,755 --> 00:27:05,757
I HAVE TO BUY INTO YOUR PREMISE

00:27:05,757 --> 00:27:08,193
THAT PUTTING AN INDICATOR
FOR CAFFEINE

00:27:08,193 --> 00:27:10,195
IS GOING TO
SIGNIFICANTLY INCREASE

00:27:10,195 --> 00:27:12,364
THE NUMBER OF TIMES
PEOPLE USE MY PACKET.

00:27:12,364 --> 00:27:14,366
I THINK THAT'S A GIVEN.
ABSOLUTELY.

00:27:14,366 --> 00:27:16,835
HOWEVER,
THERE'S ANOTHER ANGLE.

00:27:16,835 --> 00:27:19,171
WHAT IS IT?

00:27:19,171 --> 00:27:22,941
WHAT IF I DON'T WANT MY‐‐
MY COMPETITION TO HAVE THIS?

00:27:22,941 --> 00:27:24,576
AND THEY BURY IT.

00:27:24,576 --> 00:27:28,780
YOU KNOW, THERE'S SOMETHING
NASTY ABOUT YOU I REALLY LIKE.

00:27:28,780 --> 00:27:32,017
(Robert laughs)
OH. (chuckles) I'M... I THINK
I'M HAPPY TO HEAR THAT.

00:27:32,017 --> 00:27:33,519
NO, NO, I LIKE IT.

00:27:33,519 --> 00:27:35,921
WHAT YOU'RE TRYING TO DO
IS CREATE A BIDDING WAR

00:27:35,921 --> 00:27:38,357
IN A VERY,
VERY STRUCTURED MARKET.
AND SPEAKING PLAINLY,

00:27:38,357 --> 00:27:40,826
THERE'S THE FEEDING FRENZY.
RIGHT.

00:27:40,826 --> 00:27:42,828
WHAT DO YOU DO FOR A LIVING?

00:27:42,828 --> 00:27:45,097
CURRENTLY, I'M A MECHANICAL
ENGINEER. I'M IN BETWEEN.

00:27:45,097 --> 00:27:47,099
AND SOME DAY‐TRADING
IN THE MARKET.

00:27:47,099 --> 00:27:49,301
AND WHERE DID YOU GET
THIS IDEA FROM?

00:27:49,301 --> 00:27:51,436
I WAS ON A BUSINESS TRIP
AND, 11:00 AT NIGHT,

00:27:51,436 --> 00:27:53,438
I STOPPED WITH MY WIFE
AND SAID,

00:27:53,438 --> 00:27:55,874
"LET'S HAVE A SLICE OF PIE
AND CUP OF COFFEE."

00:27:55,874 --> 00:27:58,944
I HAD A BUSINESS MEETING
THE NEXT DAY.

00:27:58,944 --> 00:28:02,681
I WAS UP ALL NIGHT, AND I <i>KNOW</i>
SHE DIDN'T GIVE ME DECAF.

00:28:02,681 --> 00:28:06,018
BUT THERE'S ONLY ONE WAY TO
TELL, AND THAT'S TO DRINK IT.
SO WHAT'S WITH THE $200,000?

00:28:06,018 --> 00:28:09,655
IT'S JUST A NUMBER
YOU PULLED OUT OF THE AIR?
THERE IS, UM, UH,
LICENSING FEES,

00:28:09,655 --> 00:28:11,657
THERE'S ATTORNEY FEES,
AS YOU KNOW,

00:28:11,657 --> 00:28:13,659
AND WE HAVE TO
SET UP A CORPORATION.

00:28:13,659 --> 00:28:16,395
AND I NEED SOME HELP. I NEED
YOU GUYS TO OPEN UP DOORS.

00:28:16,395 --> 00:28:19,898
IF ONE OF YOU ARE INTERESTED,
I WANT TO ADVANCE THIS.

00:28:19,898 --> 00:28:22,534
I WANT TO MOVE IT FORWARD.
(Barbara) I'M GONNA JUMP IN‐‐

00:28:22,534 --> 00:28:24,102
I'LL‐‐
IN HERE,

00:28:24,102 --> 00:28:27,206
BECAUSE I THINK THERE ARE TWO
REAL WEAKNESSES TO THIS IDEA.

00:28:27,206 --> 00:28:30,042
I'M NOT SURE THE CONSUMER
IS THAT PARANOID

00:28:30,042 --> 00:28:32,044
ABOUT TESTING AND MISTRUSTING
WHETHER THEY GOT

00:28:32,044 --> 00:28:34,413
CAFFEINATED COFFEE
OR DECAFFEINATED COFFEE‐‐

00:28:34,413 --> 00:28:36,915
THAT'S ONE‐‐
AND THE SECOND REASON IS,

00:28:36,915 --> 00:28:39,151
WITH ANY OF THESE
PROSPECTIVE BUYERS

00:28:39,151 --> 00:28:41,153
YOU'RE HOPING TO SELL TO,

00:28:41,153 --> 00:28:44,156
IT'S NOT JUST THE MINIMAL COST
OF ADDING IT TO THE PACKET.

00:28:44,156 --> 00:28:46,158
BUT THEY'VE GOT TO MARKET
THE IDEA

00:28:46,158 --> 00:28:48,994
AND LET THE CONSUMER KNOW,
AND THAT'S EXPENSIVE.

00:28:48,994 --> 00:28:52,064
IT'S NOT SUCH AN EASY,
CLEAR ROAD TO MY MIND

00:28:52,064 --> 00:28:53,565
AS YOU'RE POSITIONING IT.

00:28:53,565 --> 00:28:57,603
SO FOR THOSE TWO REASONS ONLY,
I'M OUT.

00:28:57,603 --> 00:29:00,205
THOSE ARE EXCELLENT POINTS,
BARBARA.

00:29:00,205 --> 00:29:02,541
AND I THINK THAT'S WHY
MICHAEL REALIZES,

00:29:02,541 --> 00:29:04,676
HIS 25% IS LUDICROUS.

00:29:06,511 --> 00:29:08,647
(O'Leary) THAT SOUNDS LIKE
A NEGOTIATION, ROBERT.

00:29:08,647 --> 00:29:11,917
THAT'S LIKE BASICALLY SAYING
THAT YOU'LL DO THIS DEAL,

00:29:11,917 --> 00:29:14,987
BUT YOU WANT MORE THAN 25%,
AND YOUR GREED IS SHOWING.

00:29:14,987 --> 00:29:18,156
THAT SHOULD BE
FAMILIAR TO YOU.
I SAW YOUR GREED.
I SAW YOUR GREED.

00:29:18,156 --> 00:29:21,226
YOU KNOW, MIKE, I WAS
ON THE FENCE FOR A SECOND,

00:29:21,226 --> 00:29:24,062
BUT I AGREE WITH BARBARA
THAT THEY WOULD HAVE TO DO

00:29:24,062 --> 00:29:26,064
VERY POINTED
AND SPECIFIC MARKETING.

00:29:26,064 --> 00:29:28,400
I LIKE THE IDEA
THAT YOU'RE TRYING TO ATTACK

00:29:28,400 --> 00:29:30,902
THE NUMBER ONE DRUG
SOLD IN THE WORLD.

00:29:30,902 --> 00:29:33,171
BUT I AM OUT.

00:29:33,171 --> 00:29:35,140
MICHAEL, I'LL PAY FOR AN OPTION

00:29:35,140 --> 00:29:38,810
TO SEE IF ONE
OF THE FIVE GUYS DO IT.

00:29:41,079 --> 00:29:43,415
I'LL GIVE YOU THE $200,000
FOR...

00:29:43,415 --> 00:29:45,150
60%...

00:29:47,452 --> 00:29:50,822
CONTINGENT ON GETTING A DEAL
WITH ONE OF THE FIVE COMPANIES.

00:29:50,822 --> 00:29:52,491
♪♪

00:29:52,491 --> 00:29:55,360
MICHAEL, I HAVE
A BETTER OFFER.

00:29:55,360 --> 00:29:58,363
♪♪

00:30:08,540 --> 00:30:11,143
♪♪

00:30:11,143 --> 00:30:12,644
<i>TWO SHARKS ARE OUT.</i>

00:30:12,644 --> 00:30:16,415
<i>ROBERT HAS OFFERED $200,000</i>
<i>FOR A 60% STAKE</i>

00:30:16,415 --> 00:30:20,786
<i>CONTINGENT UPON GETTING A DEAL</i>
<i>WITH A MAJOR SWEETENER COMPANY.</i>

00:30:20,786 --> 00:30:23,422
<i>BUT KEVIN HARRINGTON</i>
<i>IS ALSO INTERESTED.</i>

00:30:23,422 --> 00:30:25,791
MICHAEL, I HAVE
A BETTER OFFER.

00:30:25,791 --> 00:30:27,726
SAME CONTINGENCY,

00:30:27,726 --> 00:30:31,496
BUT I'LL‐‐I'LL MAKE YOU
THE OFFER AT 50%.

00:30:31,496 --> 00:30:34,232
ALL THE OFFERS ARE CONTINGENT.

00:30:34,232 --> 00:30:37,669
IT'S WORTHLESS
IF THEY DON'T WANT IT.
BUT WE ALL AGREED ON THAT.

00:30:37,669 --> 00:30:41,206
BUT YOU'VE GOT TWO OFFERS,
OKAY?
NOW I'M DECIDING WHETHER
TO TRUMP BOTH OF YOU BOZOS.

00:30:41,206 --> 00:30:43,942
♪♪

00:30:43,942 --> 00:30:47,012
MM.

00:30:47,012 --> 00:30:49,214
O'LEARY, ARE YOU IN,
ARE YOU OUT?

00:30:49,214 --> 00:30:51,483
I AM THINKING.
I DON'T NEED THE NOISE.

00:30:51,483 --> 00:30:55,220
♪♪

00:30:55,220 --> 00:30:58,924
I THINK YOU NEED TO EITHER
SAY YES TO ME OR YES TO ROBERT.

00:30:58,924 --> 00:31:03,695
'CAUSE I DON'T HEAR ANY OFFERS
COMING OUT OF MR. O'LEARY.

00:31:03,695 --> 00:31:07,332
NOW WHAT ARE WE WAITING FOR?
MICHAEL, YOU'VE GOT TWO OFFERS.

00:31:07,332 --> 00:31:10,168
I NEED AN ANSWER. I'M GONNA
TAKE MY OFFER OFF THE TABLE.

00:31:10,168 --> 00:31:13,472
I NEED AN ANSWER ON MY OFFER.

00:31:13,472 --> 00:31:15,907
OH.

00:31:15,907 --> 00:31:17,342
UM...

00:31:17,342 --> 00:31:21,513
I BELIEVE THAT I WOULD TAKE
THE 50% PARTNERSHIP.

00:31:21,513 --> 00:31:24,850
ARE YOU ACCEPTING MY OFFER
THEN, MICHAEL?
I'LL ACCEPT YOUR OFFER.

00:31:24,850 --> 00:31:27,486
OKAY. THANK YOU.
ALL RIGHT. GOOD JOB.
(Barbara) NICE JOB.

00:31:27,486 --> 00:31:30,455
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.
THANK YOU VERY MUCH.
NICE TO BE PARTNERS.

00:31:30,455 --> 00:31:34,126
IT WAS A FAIR DEAL.
IT WAS A FAIR DEAL.
THANK YOU VERY MUCH
FOR YOUR TIME.

00:31:34,126 --> 00:31:37,062
WHAT JUST HAPPENED? YOU NEVER
EVEN GAVE AN OFFER, DID YOU?
(Robert) I JUST NEEDED‐‐
I JUST NEEDED CONTROL.

00:31:37,062 --> 00:31:40,165
HE'S JUST MOUTHING OFF.
(Harrington)
I WASN'T GIVING HIM A CHANCE.

00:31:40,165 --> 00:31:43,135
I SAID IF HE ACCEPTS MY OFFER,
IT'S A DEAL. WE'RE DONE.
NO, I GOT IT.

00:31:43,135 --> 00:31:46,104
I JUST‐‐JUST‐‐
SOMEBODY KEPT HIM QUIET.
I WASN'T QUITE THERE.

00:31:46,104 --> 00:31:48,106
DAYMOND, YOU KNOW
WHAT I'VE LEARNED?

00:31:48,106 --> 00:31:50,275
TALK IS CHEAP,
AND SO IS KEVIN O'LEARY.

00:31:50,275 --> 00:31:52,744
(sharks laugh)

00:31:52,744 --> 00:31:54,479
I FEEL LIKE FINALLY...

00:31:54,479 --> 00:31:57,482
AFTER 18 YEARS OF KEEPING
THIS THING BOTTLED UP,

00:31:57,482 --> 00:31:59,551
I FINALLY PARTNERED
WITH THE RIGHT MAN

00:31:59,551 --> 00:32:01,553
TO HELP ME BRING THIS
TO FRUITION.

00:32:01,553 --> 00:32:04,022
IT'S GREAT!
I FEEL EXCITED.

00:32:04,022 --> 00:32:07,025
<i>NEXT INTO THE SHARK TANK</i>
<i>ARE JEFF AND ANNIE HUGHES,</i>

00:32:07,025 --> 00:32:09,027
<i>A HUSBAND‐AND‐WIFE TEAM</i>

00:32:09,027 --> 00:32:11,263
<i>WITH A NEW TWIST</i>
<i>TO AN OLD PROFESSION.</i>

